00:48:03.610 --> 00:48:08.000
out all the story about his life,
going to Europe, [inaudible].

00:48:09.370 --> 00:48:11.420
&gt;&gt; Layla Diba: Well, there-- yes.

00:48:11.420 --> 00:48:14.590
There is a-- there is a--
I wouldn't say enormous,

00:48:14.590 --> 00:48:17.060
but a substantial bibliography

00:48:17.060 --> 00:48:21.250
and I was mentioning
earlier well before I came

00:48:21.250 --> 00:48:24.270
to the field there was a
scholar called Sohali Honsari

00:48:24.270 --> 00:48:25.570
[assumed spelling].

00:48:25.570 --> 00:48:26.870
You may remember him, Your Majesty.

00:48:26.870 --> 00:48:30.710
And he wrote a very
comprehensive book on Kamal al Mulk

00:48:30.710 --> 00:48:39.870
and reproduced many of the works
and I can base a lot of my remarks

00:48:39.870 --> 00:48:44.000
on that book, but also
amazingly, again,

00:48:44.000 --> 00:48:50.550
Kamal al Mulk himself left his
memoirs, wrote about 10 pages

00:48:50.550 --> 00:48:55.120
in his own hand and these
were published in the memoirs

00:48:55.120 --> 00:48:58.770
of Dr. Ghasem Ghani,
Cyrus Ghani's father,

00:48:58.770 --> 00:49:01.250
which Cyrus then published
in eight volumes.

00:49:01.250 --> 00:49:07.190
So, we have the painter's own
account and when I read these,

00:49:07.190 --> 00:49:10.990
I was reading the name of
this painter, Gordigiani,

00:49:10.990 --> 00:49:12.690
I said this can't be right.

00:49:12.690 --> 00:49:14.570
You know? He must have
misunderstood.

00:49:14.570 --> 00:49:19.400
How could-- what a strange name,
gorgeous dawn, you know, Florence,

00:49:19.400 --> 00:49:21.660
but I went-- there--
you know, there are--

00:49:21.660 --> 00:49:26.160
there are books of famous
artists, Tina Becker is known

00:49:26.160 --> 00:49:28.680
as the bible of-- every
artist is listed--

00:49:28.680 --> 00:49:32.590
and Kamal al Mulk gave
the correct spelling

00:49:32.590 --> 00:49:34.140
and then we tracked this down.

00:49:34.140 --> 00:49:38.610
So, his own memoirs are
a very valuable resource

00:49:38.610 --> 00:49:42.470
that scholars have not used
enough and they didn't realize--

00:49:42.470 --> 00:49:46.160
I mean there are incredible
nuggets in there and he talks

00:49:46.160 --> 00:49:49.930
about his relationship with
the ruler and he was accused

00:49:49.930 --> 00:49:53.580
at one point of stealing something
from the [inaudible] because--

00:49:53.580 --> 00:49:57.810
I mean it was very
personal and so his memoirs,

00:49:57.810 --> 00:50:01.490
even though they are 10
pages long, they're very,

00:50:01.490 --> 00:50:03.700
very informative about his life.

00:50:03.700 --> 00:50:07.500
But-- so, there's been
a lot of scholarship.

00:50:07.500 --> 00:50:16.500 position:56%
